mode: linked, //Other possible values are slideshow, linked, web.auto: on, //Specifies whether to start the presentation automatically.loop: on, //Specifies whether the presentation will loop back to the beginning automatically after reaching //the last view. Only relevant for presentation and slideshow modes.hide_elements: no, //hide presentation element after transition to a new slideback: end, //Another possible value is start. The setting specifies how elements are handled when going // backwards in a presentation. end shows the previous slide at its last element order, while start shows // the previous slide at the 0 position, requiring the user to step thought the elements again.spot_size: 10, // Presentation views can be defined with an elliptical shape, called a spot. When using a // spot, the show is scaled so that the spot has a fix pixel size. This setting defines its the target pixel size.transition: slide, //Defines the default transition between the views. This is the transition used when one is // not specified in the view definition.enter: appear, //Defines the default entrance effect for view elements.exit: disappear, //Defines the default exit effect for view elements.html_target: _blank, //Sets default target for external links. Values can be _blank, _self, _parent, _top. bar_size: 0:0:0:0, //Overrides the sizes of the top, right, bottom and left bars around the display.video_reorder: true, // Only re levant if video elements in the presentation overlap. If true, the currently // active video is positioned on top, so that it is fully visible.video_mode: single, //Other possible values are other_muted and together.
Copy these to “IA Presenter Def” layerfor easy definition of Regions and Spots
